# NextUp

**A full-stack task and habit platform that plans your day, nudges your streaks, and reminds you before you forget — not after.**

[![Django REST Framework](https://img.shields.io/badge/backend-Django%20REST%20Framework-0C4B33?style=flat-square&logo=django)](#tech-stack)
[![React + Vite](https://img.shields.io/badge/frontend-React%20%2B%20Vite-149ECA?style=flat-square&logo=react)](#tech-stack)
[![PostgreSQL](https://img.shields.io/badge/database-PostgreSQL-336791?style=flat-square&logo=postgresql)](#tech-stack)
[![Groq AI](https://img.shields.io/badge/AI-Groq-F2A93B?style=flat-square)](#tech-stack)
[![Docker](https://img.shields.io/badge/infra-Docker%20Compose-2496ED?style=flat-square&logo=docker)](#tech-stack)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-8B8D98?style=flat-square)](#license)

</div>

## What it does

|                       |                                                                                                                |
| --------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 🧠 **AI Suggestions** | Groq-powered task planning — describe what's on your plate, get structured, prioritized tasks back in seconds. |
| ✅ **Habits**         | Presets backed by a real Kaggle habit dataset, so you're never starting from a blank text field.               |
| 🔔 **Nudges**         | A scheduled command reviews your week and uses AI to write a nudge — only when you actually need one.          |
| 📧 **Reminders**      | Gmail SMTP delivery via a dedicated management command, so due dates don't slide by quietly.                   |
| 📊 **Analytics**      | Heatmaps of real progress — see consistency at a glance instead of digging through a task list.                |
| 🔐 **Sessions**       | Rotating JWT refresh handled centrally, with deduplicated refresh calls so you're never logged out mid-task.   |

---

## Tech stack

<table>
<tr><th>Layer</th><th>Tools</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Backend</b></td><td>Django · Django REST Framework · SimpleJWT · PostgreSQL</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Frontend</b></td><td>React · Vite · Tailwind CSS</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>AI / Data</b></td><td>Groq API · Kaggle dataset (habit presets)</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Infra</b></td><td>Docker Compose · GitHub Actions CI/CD · Gmail SMTP</td></tr>
</table>

---

## Architecture

```
React / Vite  →  DRF + JWT  →  PostgreSQL  →  Reminders · Nudges
   (client)         (API)         (data)          (jobs)
```

<details>
<summary><b>More on the moving parts</b></summary>
<br>

- **Client** — React/Vite frontend with a centralized `api.js` request wrapper, automatic token refresh, and a `SessionWatcher` for session-expired redirects.
- **API** — Django REST Framework, JWT auth via SimpleJWT, Groq integration for task/habit suggestions.
- **Data** — PostgreSQL, with models for tasks, habits, and notifications.
- **Jobs** — `send_reminders` (Gmail SMTP) and `check_habit_consistency` (Groq-based weekly nudges), both run as Django management commands.

</details>

---

## Getting started

**1. Clone and configure**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/nextup.git
cd nextup
cp .env.example .env
```

**2. Set your secrets** — see [environment variables](#environment-variables) below.

**3. Run the stack**

```bash
docker compose up --build
```

**4. Open it**

| Service  | URL                       |
| -------- | ------------------------- |
| Frontend | http://localhost:5173     |
| API      | http://localhost:8000/api |

---

## Environment variables

| Variable              | Description                                                              |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `DATABASE_URL`        | PostgreSQL connection string, e.g. `postgres://user:pass@db:5432/nextup` |
| `GROQ_API_KEY`        | API key for Groq AI task/habit suggestions                               |
| `EMAIL_HOST_USER`     | Gmail address used to send reminder emails                               |
| `EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD` | Gmail App Password (not your regular password)                           |

